      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Custom equality check. Two messages are equal if and only if they have the same key, the same severity, and the same properties. The order of properties is not considered.
        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        True of the parameter object equals this message, false otherwise

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()
        Custom hash code calculation algorithm. The hash code for a message is determined by the key, severity, and properties. As with equals, property ordering is irrelevant, i.e. two messages with the same key and severity and properties will return a consistent hash code value no matter how the properties are ordered. If the message does not contain a key and severity, the default Java object hash code is returned.
        Overrides:
        hashCode in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        The hash code value for this message
